          <li>Founders Dr Christopher and Mary Penfolds planted their vine cuttings they had carried on their voyage over to Australia.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>1870
        <ul>
          <li>As the company grew, Dr Penfold‚Äôs medical practice grew too so Mary Penfolds and the winery and assumed total control on his death in 1870. She ran it until she retired 14 years later.  When she retired she left management to her daughter Georgina.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>1907
        <ul>
          <li>Penfolds becomes Australia‚Äôs largest winery</li>
        </ul>
